mic biases embedded in many aspects of human resources management practices. Opening Doors to Diversity in Leadership provides evidence and options for businesses to build a more diverse workforce, leadership team, and corporate culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aDiversity in the workplace. 0aLeadership. 4aDISCOUNT-C. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Management.2bisacsh  aHR.  adiversity.  aemployment.  aequity.  ahuman resources.  aleadership.  amanagement.  apeople management.  atraining.  aworkplace.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073922040uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148751197540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487511975423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487511975/original  a978-3-11-073922-0  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles